ZH: 他付了饭钱。
EN: He paid for the meal.

ZH: 她付了房租。
EN: She paid the rent.

ZH: 我们应该付账。
EN: We should pay the bill.

ZH: 你能帮我付一下吗？
EN: Can you help me pay?

ZH: 我付不起这笔账。
EN: I can't afford to pay this bill.

ZH: 他每个月都要付车贷。
EN: He has to pay the car loan every month.

ZH: 她不习惯付现金。
EN: She is not used to paying in cash.

ZH: 我要去银行付款。
EN: I need to go to the bank to make a payment.

ZH: 他拒绝付小费。
EN: He refuses to pay the tip.

ZH: 为了生活费，我必须每月付房租。
EN: I have to pay the rent every month for living expenses.

ZH: 她是个吝啬鬼，从来都不愿意付钱。
EN: She is a miser, never willing to pay.

ZH: 他答应明天付钱。
EN: He promised to pay the money tomorrow.

ZH: 我刚才付网费了。
EN: I just paid the internet fee.

ZH: 请在报名截止日期前付费。
EN: Please pay the fee before the registration deadline.

ZH: 我今天要去店里付款。
EN: I'm going to the store today to make a payment.

ZH: 她经常忘记付账。
EN: She often forgets to pay the bill.

ZH: 我付账单的时候，发现有一项错误。
EN: When I paid the bill, I found a mistake in it.

ZH: 如果你不付押金，无法预订这个场地。
EN: You can't book this venue without paying a deposit.

ZH: 他承诺下个月付清所有欠款。
EN: He promised to pay off all debts next month.
